  "name": "Digital Rectal Exam",
  "description": "This test case evaluates a complex phenotype algorithm for identifying digital rectal examination (DRE) cases in prostate cancer patients. It requires finding male patients over 35 with prostate cancer diagnosis, then searching clinical notes for DRE documentation within a specific timeframe relative to treatment initiation. This represents a quality care metric phenotype that combines structured data (diagnosis codes, demographics) with unstructured clinical note analysis and temporal constraints.",
  "prompt": "Find all male patients aged 35 or older with prostate cancer who have documentation of digital rectal examination performed within 6 months before their first prostate cancer treatment.",
